Looking at the proof goal, I need to prove that `0 ≤ x.abs` for any rational `x`.

The definition of `Rat.abs` is `if x < 0 then -x else x`, so I need to handle two cases:
1. If `x < 0`, then `x.abs = -x`, and I need `0 ≤ -x`
2. If `¬(x < 0)`, then `x.abs = x`, and I need `0 ≤ x`

I can use the `Rat.nonneg_total` theorem which states `0 ≤ x ∨ 0 ≤ -x`, and `Rat.not_lt` to convert between `¬(x < 0)` and `0 ≤ x`.

```lean
